text: Hey guys it’s Ro!

So many things happened in 2015 and I wanted
to make a recap video of some of
my favorite memories!

Played the Hamburger Challenge with my sister
Mo!

Cooked up some Bronut Donut holes with Ian
and Anthony of Smosh.

Tried some yummy flavors of Oreo cookies with
Mo for the Oreo Challenge game.
Baked Minecraft Pumpkin Pie with Captain Sparklez.
Adopted my very first dog ever, cookie!

My little Cookie Monster, oh my gosh I love
her so much!

Created Bomberman Cupcakes with Rhett and
Link.

Guessed which foods had sugar on Good Mythical
Morning.

Reacted to a VERY different kind of Mario
on YouTubers React.

Made the world’s worst pizza with my sister
playing the Pizza Challenge.

Traveled to Washington DC to take a meeting
with the Vice President and some
cool YouTubers!

Released my first music video Perfect Together
with Kurt Hugo Schneider.

Had an amazing perfect together premiere party
as well, we celebrated on

Valentines day with friends, fans, crew and
everyone in the video!

Geeked out about Star Trek with my favorite
Astrophysicist, Neil Degrasse Tyson.

Watched the Weirdest Video you will ever see
on YouTubers React.

Decorated Smash Brothers Cupcakes with Michelle
Phan.

Teamed up with Wilton to make 20 decorating
videos.
Tried weird canned food for the Tin Can Challenge.

Guest appeared on Radio Disney with Ali Simpson,
and they even played Perfect
Together on the Radio!

Crafted some fun DIY gifts for my Mom for
Mothers Day!
Whipped up Walking Dead cookies with Max Schneider.

Teamed up with Wayfair to give my home a much
needed makeover!
Played will it Fondue or will it Fon-Don’t!

Spent Father’s Day making treats for my
Dad.

Was named as one of Variety Magazine’s Fame
Changers.

Attended VidCon for a fan meet up and to be on a
food panel.

Enjoyed the day at Disneyland with the Nerdy
Nummies Crew.
Announced my very first cookbook.
Reacted to the Final Fantasy 7 Remake Trailer.

Grilled up some Super Hero Burgers with my
friend and fitness guru Cassey Ho.

Experienced many weird flavors of Pringles
for the Pringles Challenge.

Did the delicious French Fry Challenge with
my Sister.

Learned what it meant to be a kid again by
eating baby food with my friend
Kurt Hugo Schneider.

Got a major brain freeze while playing the Ice Cream
Challenge game with Kurt.
Reached 5 Million Subscribers on YouTube!
Finely crafted a Pizza Cake with Grace Helbig!

Attempted to guess crazy soda flavors with
Mo on the Soda Challenge.
Saw Animals in Mirrors on YouTubers react.

Got my groove on while baking My Little Pony
Cupcakes with Austin Mahone.

And continued dancing with Molly during the
Candy Assembly challenge.

Showcased my impeccable fashion sense with
Mamrie Hart while making Harry Potter drinks.

Celebrated Cookie’s First birthday by making
DIY Dog Treats, and a little doggie
birthday cake, om-yum-yum-yum! She loved it!

Was nominated for Best Food Show at the Streamy
Awards.

My friend TJ stopped by to play the Pocky
Challenge.

Lindsey Stirling helped my make delicious
Adventure Time Tarts on Nerdy Nummies.

We surpassed 1 billion total video views on
YouTube.

Survived the trivia smoothie challenge on
Cassey Ho’s Channel.

Made my friend Dawin try Red Vines for the
very first time.

Sampled nearly every flavor of Goldfish Crackers
with Cassey Ho.

Put it all together with Eva for some Costume
Quest 2 Halloween Treats.

Hannah Hart had me as a guest on My Drunk
Kitchen.

Danced in Dawin’s music video for his song
Dessert.

Brewed up some mischief with Jen Chae, to
make Hocus Pocus Cookies.

Had a fun Easy Bake Oven Bake-Off with my
sister.
And Cookie!

Produced and hosted my very first hour long
TV Special on the Cooking Channel.

Assembled a Jack Skellington Cheese Ball with
Jake Roper.
Fought off Sith as BB-8 on Jen Chae’s Channel.
Carved a pumpkin in under 5 minutes with Mo.
Had a blast and met so many of you at StreamCon.
I even got to meet Doug the Pug!

Ventured out on the Nerdy Nummies Cookbook
Bus Tour.

It was amazing living on a Tour Bus for 3-1/2
weeks and touring the country to

meet all of you guys. I still can’t believe
we visited 32 cities in under a month.

We visited: Northvale, Huntington, New York
City, Doylestown, Haverford,

Baltimore, Waldorf, Richmond, Pittsboro, Concord,
Douglasville, Jacksonville,

Kissimmee, Vero Beach, Miami, Fort Meyers,
Brandon, Pensacola, Mobile,

New Orleans, Baton Rouge, Hastings, Katy,
San Antonio, Austin, Dallas,

Grape Vine, San Francisco, Ventura, Orange,
San Diego, and lastly, my home
city, Los Angeles!

Watched a hilarious video filmed in Target
on YouTubers React.
Brewed some Nuka Cola with Hannah Hart.

Challenged my sister to the Chicken Nugget
Challenge.
Developed a recipe for 17 Magazine.

Ate way too many donuts with my friend Jake
on the Donut Challenge.
Reacted to Don’t Hug Me I’m Scared 5.

Had a 2 page spread featuring my kitchen in
Food Network Magazine.

Decorated the world’s most beautiful cake,
hmm-hmm-hmm…

With my sister while playing the Not My Arms
Challenge.

Premiered my second hour long tv special for
the holidays on The Cooking Channel.

Got to meet Kevin, Bob and Stuart from the
Minions.

Was a part of YouTube Rewind with so many
other amazing people.

Collabbed with my Superwoman, Lilly for a video:
Group Texts in Real Life.

Attended the world premiere of Star Wars The
Force Awakens and geeked out!
It was amazing!

Taught how to Make Textbook S’Mores on Hallmark
Channel’s Home and Family.
Made some delicious DIY Holiday Treats.

The very sweet and talented Megan Nicole stopped
by to make some Awkward Penguin Cookies.

Made a ton of Nerdy Nummies all throughout the
year.

Ended the year spending christmas and celebrating
the New Year in Hawaii with
my friends and family.

Alright, I hope you guys enjoyed the video
and you had a wonderful 2015,
let’s make 2016 just as fun!
Bye-bye!
